TY  - JOUR
T1  - Catalog Advertising Allocation
AU  - Sokolick, W. D.
AU  - Hartung, Philip H.
Y1  - 1969/06/01
PY  - 1969
DA  - 1969/06/01
N1  - doi: 10.1287/mnsc.15.10.B521
DO  - 10.1287/mnsc.15.10.B521
T2  - Management Science
JF  - Management Science
JO  - Management Science
SP  - B-521
EP  - B-529
VL  - 15
IS  - 10
PB  - INFORMS
N2  - The catalog advertising allocation problem is one of allocating space (pages) in a catalog to products. Different allocations of space will have different catalog preparation costs and will produce different total catalog sales. This paper presents a model to forecast the sales results of different space allocations, reports on the empirical validity of the forecasts, and then presents a model to maximize sales subject to a total catalog cost constraint.
AB  - The catalog advertising allocation problem is one of allocating space (pages) in a catalog to products. Different allocations of space will have different catalog preparation costs and will produce different total catalog sales. This paper presents a model to forecast the sales results of different space allocations, reports on the empirical validity of the forecasts, and then presents a model to maximize sales subject to a total catalog cost constraint.
